{
  "texts": [
    "We then develop MutComputeX: a structure-based self-supervised residual neural network (3DResNet) trained to generalize at protein:non-protein interfaces, which is used to generate activityenriched Nb4OMT designs from an ML-generated protein-cofactorsubstrate structure.",
    "The evolved biosensor is used to rapidly screen a panel of MutComputeX-guided Nb4OMT designs, leading to the identification of one variant that yields a 60% improvement in product titer, 2-fold higher catalytic activity, and 3-fold lower off-product formation.",
    "A newly solved crystal structure of this engineered enzyme helps elucidate the mechanism behind key beneficial mutations and highlight important discrepancies with the AlphaFold2 model.",
    "Identifying a biosensor for the branchpoint amaryllidaceae alkaloid 4′-O-methylnorbelladine 4′-O-methylnorbelladine (4NB) is the branchpoint intermediate for the entire amaryllidaceae alkaloid (AA) family (Fig. 1a), and therefore was the target compound for biosensor generation.",
    "Previously the highly malleable TetR-family Salmonella typhimurium repressor RamR had been used as a starting point for identifying biosensors for a variety of benzylisoquinoline alkaloids 17."
  ]
}